type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For all sets <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A,B,X,Y]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  X \land  B\cong  Y\implies  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}\cong  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (X,Y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3717</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#389</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-389.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>25</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00LK</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Fix <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
title="Bijection">bijections</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B \to  Y]]></fr:tex>. We will define a bijection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H\colon  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}\to  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (X,Y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Given <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex>, we define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\colon  X\mathbin {\nrightarrow } Y]]></fr:tex> to be the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IN.xml"
addr="jms-00IN"
title="Relational composite">relational composite</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  R\circ  f^{-1}]]></fr:tex>. The inverse mapping <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H^{-1}\colon \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (X,Y\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is defined to take <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S\colon  X\mathbin {\nrightarrow } Y]]></fr:tex> to the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IN.xml"
addr="jms-00IN"
title="Relational composite">relational composite</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g^{-1} \circ  S\circ  f]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Next, we check that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H^{-1}]]></fr:tex> is simulatneously a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KS.xml"
addr="jms-00KS"
title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</fr:link> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KS.xml"
addr="jms-00KS"
title="Section-retraction pair">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}    H^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (H{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} &= g^{-1}\circ  H{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  f\\    &= g^{-1}\circ  {\mathopen {}\left (g\circ  R\circ  f^{-1}\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  f\\    &= {\mathopen {}\left (g^{-1}\circ  g\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  R\circ  {\mathopen {}\left (f^{-1}\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}}\\    &= \mathsf {id}_{B}\circ  R\circ  \mathsf {id}_{A}\\    &= R    \\    H{\mathopen {}\left (H^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (S\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} &= g\circ  H^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (S\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  f^{-1}\\    &= g\circ  {\mathopen {}\left (g^{-1}\circ  S\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  f^{-1}\\    &= {\mathopen {}\left (g\circ  g^{-1}\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  S\circ {\mathopen {}\left (f\circ  f^{-1}\right )\mathclose {}}\\    &= \mathsf {id}_{Y}\circ  S\circ  \mathsf {id}_{X}\\    &= S   \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
