xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>5078</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00L4</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00L4.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Equivalence relation</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>23</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A relation <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex> is called an <fr:em><fr:strong>equivalence relation</fr:strong></fr:em> when it is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00JX.xml"
addr="jms-00JX"
title="Preorder">reflexive, transitive</fr:link>, and symmetric:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  \forall  x\in  A\mathpunct {.} x\mathrel {E}x ]]></fr:tex><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  \forall  x,y,z\in  A\mathpunct {.} x\mathrel {E} y \land  y \mathrel {E} z \implies  x \mathrel {E} z ]]></fr:tex><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  \forall  x,y\in  A\mathpunct {.} x \mathrel {E} y \implies  y\mathrel {E}x ]]></fr:tex><fr:p>We will write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {EqRel}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for the set of all equivalence relations on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
